### Email OTP Testing

## Email OTP Login Flow (Recommended)

### Step 1: Login with Email (Send OTP)
POST {{base_url}}/api/v1/auth/email/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "test@example.com"
}

###

### Step 2: Verify OTP and Get Access Token
POST {{base_url}}/api/v1/auth/email/verify
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "test@example.com",
  "otp": "123456"
}

###

## Send OTP to Email (Generic)
POST {{base_url}}/api/v1/email/send-otp
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "test@example.com",
  "expiry_minutes": 5
}

###

## Verify OTP
POST {{base_url}}/api/v1/email/verify-otp
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "test@example.com",
  "otp": "123456"
}

###

## Send Welcome Email
POST {{base_url}}/api/v1/email/send-welcome
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "test@example.com",
  "name": "John Doe"
}

###

## Send Password Reset Email
POST {{base_url}}/api/v1/email/send-password-reset
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "test@example.com",
  "reset_token": "abc123def456",
  "reset_url": "https://example.com/reset-password?token=abc123def456"
}

